Ram has 6 apples. Sita has 7 apples. How many apples are there altogether?
Scot has 6 blocks. He finds 4 more blocks. How many blocks does he have in all?
Jeff has 5 bags. He buys 5 more bags. How many bags does he have in all?
John buys 11 peaches. He eats 9 peaches. How many does John have now?
Sidd has 11 books. Paul has 9 books. How many books do they have altogether?
Lee has 4 cups. His brother takes away 3 cups from Lee. How many cups does Lee have?
Sam has 8 pencils. He finds 11 more pencils. How many pencils does he have in all?
David gave 3 candies to Ruth, and John gave 2 candies to David. Now David has 4 candies more than Ruth has. How many candies does David have now, if Ruth had 7 candies in the beginning?
Ruth had 3 apples. She put 2 apples into a basket. How many apples are there in the basket now, if in the beginning there were 4 apples in the basket?
Ruth had 5 nuts more than Dan had. Ruth gave Dan 3 nuts. Dan gave 2 nuts to David. Now Dan has 4 nuts and David has 6 nuts. How many nuts does Ruth have now?
John had 5 apples. Mary gave him 3 apples. How many apples does John have now?
Ruth has 3 dolls. Ann has 4 dolls. How many dolls do Ruth and Ann have altogether?
Sara has 6 flowers. Clara has 3 flowers more than Sara. How many flowers does Clara have ?
Angela had 8 computer games. She got 3 computer games more for her birthday. How many computer games does Angela have?
Jose has 7 caps. He gets 2 caps from Rebecca. How many caps does Jose end with?
There are 4 girls and 8 boys in a library. How many kids are there altogether?
Dan found 857 seashells on the beach. He gave Nancy 226 of the seashells. How many seashells does he now have ?
Sara has 122 books. Sally has 129 books. How many books do they have together ?
Sandy had 611 baseball cards, and 5 were torn. Alyssa bought 379 baseball cards from Sandy. How many baseball cards does Sandy have now ?
Tom has 812 blue marbles, he gave Sam 589 of the marbles. How many blue marbles does he now have ?
There are 120 erasers and 105 rulers in the drawer. Sandy placed 112 more erasers in the drawer. How many erasers are now there in the drawer ?
Jason had 137 nickels and 845 pennies in his bank. His dad borrowed 509 pennies from Jason. How many pennies does Jason have now?
Sara picked 138 apples and Alyssa picked 139 apples from the apple tree. How many apples were picked altogether ?
Dan grew 108 cantelopes and 121 carrots. Mike grew 100 cantelopes. How many cantelopes did they grow in all ?
There are 127 maple trees and 114 walnut trees currently in the park. The park will have 108 more maple trees. How many maple trees will the park have?
A fruit vendor bought 45 apples and 60 oranges. How many fruits did the vendor buy in all?
